title: Photograph, View of the nave and chancel of an unidentified church, 1904–13
title_raw: View of the nave and chancel of an unidentified church
description:
Designed by Leon Dabo (1868–1960); for J. and R. Lamb Co.
Horizontal rectangle: View from back of nave, high, to the altar. Pointed arches on clustered columns along both sides of nave, chancel of three blind pointed arches behind the altar and Gothic revival altar. Stained glass windows over each arch. Lower and right three large statues in niches in the reredos; spires above them.

Upper corner gone. Same church as 1961-83-17 & -18.

tombstone.epitaph:
Photograph, View of the nave and chancel of an unidentified church, 1904–13. Printed on sensitized paper.
